      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): add Authorization header to provider preflight probe",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThe cron job preflight check sends `GET {baseUrl}/models` to verify local provider connectivity before running a job, but was doing so **without an Authorization header**. For providers behind auth middleware (LiteLLM, vLLM, etc.), this generates spurious 401 errors on every cron run.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`model-preflight.runtime.ts` → `probeLocalProviderEndpoint()` called `fetchWithSsrFGuard` with `init: { method: \"GET\" }` — no auth header.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdded Authorization header from the provider's API key, resolved from the same sources as normal inference calls (config apiKey → auth-profiles.json → env var).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### Before (LiteLLM proxy log, 2026-05-18)\n```\nINFO: 127.0.0.1:54237 - \"GET /models HTTP/1.1\" 401 Unauthorized\nINFO: 127.0.0.1:54452 - \"POST /chat/completions HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n```\n\n### After (LiteLLM proxy log, 2026-05-18)\n```\nINFO: 127.0.0.1:57749 - \"GET /models HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\nINFO: 127.0.0.1:57751 - \"POST /chat/completions HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n```\n\nBoth requests now carry the same Authorization header, confirmed by sequential source ports (57749 → 57751) from the same process. Tested on a live OpenClaw 2026.5.12 gateway with LiteLLM proxy.\n\n## Changes\n\n`src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.ts`:\n- Added `resolveProbeApiKey()` that resolves API key from config apiKey, auth-profiles.json, or env var\n- `probeLocalProviderEndpoint` now receives and uses the resolved API key\n- If no key is found (authless servers like Ollama), probe proceeds without auth — same as before\n",
        "branch": "fix/cron-preflight-clean",
